{
  "texts": [
    "We fix a faithful representation G ≤ GL n (R) such that G is closed under transposition.",
    "This gives the Cartan decompositionG = K exp(𝔭),where K = G ∩ SO(n) and 𝔭 = 𝔤 ∩ Sym(n).",
    "We follow [AABC + 19, §2] for the background we need regarding G-Higgs bundles.Definition 4.4.",
    "A G-Higgs bundle is a pair, (P, Φ), where P → Σ is a holomorphic K C -principal bundle and Φ is a holomorphic section of the associated bundle K Σ ⊗ (ad P (𝔭 C)).The Hodge star on one-forms is a conformal invariant and hence makes sense on a Riemann surface Σ = (B 2, c).",
    "Since it squares to -Id T * B, the complexified cotangent bundle T * B ⊗ C splits into ±ieigenbundles."
  ]
}